Q:

How to get the value of a variable in an array?

I have this code that gets all the values from my database and puts them into an array. I want to be able to access each one individually, but when i try it says undefined. How can i do this?
var data = [];
$.getJSON('http://localhost/test/index.php', function(data) {
    for (i=0; i<data.length; i++) {
        $('#content').append('<div class="col-md-3">' + '<h4>'+data[i].name+'</h4><p>'+data[i].description+'</p></div>');
    }
});

A:

You need to use.each() method for iterating over your JSON object. Also you should not append HTML inside loop as it will create multiple elements with same ID which is invalid html structure. You may consider using jQuery template plugin or any other templating engine like handlebarsjs etc.
